statement.image:
The graph of f(x) = -(x-1)^2+3 and g(x) = 1 on the interval [-1,3].
Let f(x) = -(x-1)^2+3 and g(x) = 1, graphed below.
\begin{tikzpicture} \begin{axis}[ every tick label/.append style={font=\small}, axis x line = middle, axis y line = middle, every axis y label/.style={at={(ticklabel cs:1.15)}}, %ytick = {-4, -2, -3, -1, 1, 2, 3, 4}, y label style={at={(axis description cs:.25,1.15)},anchor=north}, ylabel = {$f(x)$}, ymin = -1.5, ymax = 4.5, every axis x label/.style= {at ={(ticklabel cs:1)}}, %xtick = {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4}, x label style={at={(axis description cs:1.1,.25)},anchor=east}, xlabel = {$x$}, xmax = 3.5 ] \addplot[thick, domain = -1:3.5] {-1*(x-1)^2+3} node[midway, yshift = 18pt, xshift = -2pt] {$f(x)$}; \addplot[thick, domain = -1:3.5] {1} node[midway, yshift = -10pt] {$g(x)$}; \end{axis} \end{tikzpicture}

image.latex-image:

\begin{tikzpicture}
	\begin{axis}[
	every tick label/.append style={font=\small},
	axis x line = middle,
	axis y line = middle,
		every axis y label/.style={at={(ticklabel cs:1.15)}},
		%ytick = {-4, -2, -3, -1, 1, 2, 3, 4},
	y label style={at={(axis description cs:.25,1.15)},anchor=north},
		ylabel = {$f(x)$},
		ymin = -1.5, ymax = 4.5,
		every axis x label/.style= {at ={(ticklabel cs:1)}},
		%xtick = {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4},
		x label style={at={(axis description cs:1.1,.25)},anchor=east},
		xlabel = {$x$},
		xmax = 3.5, xmin = -1
]
	\addplot[thick, domain = -1:3.5, name path = f] {-1*(x-1)^2+3} node[midway, yshift = 18pt, xshift = -2pt] {$f(x)$};
	\addplot[thick, domain = -1:3.5, name path = g] {1} node[midway, yshift = -10pt] {$g(x)$};
	\addplot[draw=none, name path = axis] {0};
	\addplot[gray, fill opacity = 0.5] fill between[of=f and axis, soft clip = {domain=0:2}];
\end{axis}
\end{tikzpicture}


